<TITLE> SB catch nets JMB splinter group leaders </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 2 (bdnews24.com)Police arrested two suspected JMB militants Thursday in a sting that also netted two alleged leaders of a newly formed splinter group known as 'Islam and Muslim'. The new group was formed by trained militants who were formerly members of Jamaat-ul-Mujahideen Bangladesh, said a statement given to reporters at a press briefing in the capital's Special Branch office. Islam and Muslim's chief organiser Abdur Rahim, alias Shahadat, and regional commander Shajedur Rahman, alias Hanif, who was also an associate of Bangla Bhai have been arrested, said the statement. The Special Branch made the arrests at Jaydebpur in Gazipur and Baghmara in Rajshahi from June 28 to 30. Some Jihad literature was also seized. During the raids the SB also detained Jalaluddin, the Baghmara thana JMB commander in Rajshahi with a crude Indian made gun and five bullets. Earlier, they arrested Mostafizur Rahman Montu, another associate of Bangla Bhai, from Fakirerpool in the capital. Montu already stands convicted for 31 years. All of the detained denied any wrongdoing. bd
